This paper deals with the problem of detecting faulty sensors in a system using particle filter state estimation algorithm. The paper discusses the use of sensors in the built environment and their role in state estimation and control of related systems. The paper does not require a model of faulty sensor behavior, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the use of particle filter algorithm suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the accuracy of state estimation, which suggests that it could belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of detecting faulty behavior, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
